008535PD.title: Archbishop Mannix addressing the crowd at the laying of the foundation stone for extensions to St Mary's Cathedral
008535PD.text: published in the Western Mail 29 April 1926, p.3 (Supplement) with caption: The Most Rev. Dr Mannix D.D. (Archbishop of Melbourne) speaking. Among those on the platform are the Most Rev. Patrick Clune C.S.S.R. D.D. (Archbishop of Perth), Most Rev. Francis M. Redwood (Archbishop of Wellington, N.Z.), Most Rev. R. W. Spence, D. D. (Archbishop of Adelaide), Most Rev. J. Duhig D.D. (Archbishop of Brisbane), Most Rev. M. Sheehan (Coadjutor Archbishop of Sydney) and the bishops of Sandhurst, Wilcannia-Forbes, Ballarat and Port Augusta.
